data.description: MOTIVATED SELLER, Seller offering $10,000.00 TOWARDS CLOSING COSTS.  Welcome to the McElhannon House. This 1890 Victorian is in the downtown Historic District of Jefferson on just over half an acre. The full front porch provides a welcoming entryway to the home and the porch swing offers a peaceful spot to relax, enjoy the outdoors and watch the world go by. There are 5 bedrooms and 2 full baths with an additional flex/office space. the primary suite is on the main floor with a secondary bedroom as well. Formal LR with 2 sets of pocket doors, adding, adding elegance and versatility to the space. Formal Dr has a lovely built-in window seat. The kitchen has an entry from the driveway through the mud room.  There are 3 bedrooms upstairs with flex space, laundry, and full bathroom. There is a lovely sitting area in the large hallway a the top of the stairs.  8 coal fireplaces in this home. the spacious back deck is perfect for outdoor gatherings , with a covered grill area allowing you to cook outdoors regardless of the weather. There is a cute dog exit with walkway off the deck into a fenced area that ensures the safety of your pets. Children will surely enjoy the playhouse & the slide.  The slide adds an element of fun and adventure as it takes them from the deck and deposits them at the front of the playhouse. The backyard area, surrounded by trees, offers a peaceful and serene setting where you can relax, enjoy nature and spend quality time with family & friends. Also included in the sale of this home are all kitchen appliances, and the washer and dryer. HVAC dual units were replaced in June of 2022.
